                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-264-victim2162 t18320906-264-viclabel1482"></join> to Messrs. Helps and Co., of Cheapside. On the 12th of July, between ten and eleven o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18320906-264-crimeloc1483">Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-264-crimeloc1483" type="placeName" value="Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-264-crimeloc1483" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-264-off1480 t18320906-264-crimeloc1483"></join>, opposite Brooke-street, and felt something at my pocket - I turned round immediately, and saw my handkerchief under the prisoner's jacket; I saw nobody with him - I attempted to seize him, but missed my hold, and he dropped the handkerchief - he got out of my sight, but the officer pursued him - I took up my handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-264-person2164">
                  JAMES 
                  SLOGDEN
               <interp inst="t18320906-264-person2164" type="surname" value="SLOGDEN"></interp>
